<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='580639' id='t-580639'>hundreds of studies, and there's some really compelling findings.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 9:55
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='584620' id='t-584620'>The first is, we're really bad at detecting deception,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='587856' id='t-587856'>really bad. Fifty-four percent accuracy on average when you have to tell</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='591972' id='t-591972'>if somebody that just said a statement is lying or not.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='595356' id='t-595356'>That's really bad. Why is it so bad?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='598548' id='t-598548'>Well it has to do with Pinocchio's nose.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='601078' id='t-601078'>If I were to ask you guys, what do you rely on</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='603437' id='t-603437'>when you're looking at somebody and you want to find out</span>
