<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='633660' id='t-633660'>their pitch goes up, their body movements change a little bit,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='637164' id='t-637164'>but not all the time, not for everybody, it's not reliable.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='641996' id='t-641996'>Strange. The other thing is that just because you can't see me</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='645374' id='t-645374'>doesn't mean I'm going to lie. It's common sense,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='647793' id='t-647793'>but one important finding is that we lie for a reason.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='650700' id='t-650700'>We lie to protect ourselves or for our own gain</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='653067' id='t-653067'>or for somebody else's gain.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='655894' id='t-655894'>So there are some pathological liars, but they make up</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='657824' id='t-657824'>a tiny portion of the population. We lie for a reason.</span>
